Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Strengths and weaknesses of KNN", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.77909695158871*^9, 3.779096954932612*^9}, {
  3.779098662137641*^9, 3.77909866795396*^9}, {3.779105846256219*^9, 
  3.779105848592031*^9}, {3.781254600827013*^9, 
  3.7812546017158318`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6c92c1ca-96a6-4d17-85c9-\
0c6cbfe03c1e"],

Cell["\<\
Based on its simplicity and typically good performance, KNN is often a first \
choice for classification.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779100096491976*^9, 3.779100143020578*^9}, {
  3.779100246438739*^9, 3.77910024740644*^9}, {3.7791045439866047`*^9, 
  3.779104590722766*^9}, {3.7812546086128516`*^9, 
  3.7812546093270454`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"87a6e6f6-197e-42f4-b498-\
c0c2b188ceff"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Strengths", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779098865917625*^9, 
  3.779098868893455*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0db82463-3f2c-41a7-8da8-\
6c57e66ffeab"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Simple and effective", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779098882221751*^9, 
  3.779098886368268*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"eb45f96f-acf0-4f14-8ea0-\
c34f861caf34"],

Cell["It just uses the data without assuming anything on it.", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779098882221751*^9, 3.779098942925747*^9}, 
   3.781351349400875*^9, {3.781411411420308*^9, 
   3.7814114130261908`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8f05a1ef-98b6-415f-8deb-\
e3f54eec5c6a"],

Cell["Fast training phase", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779098882221751*^9, 3.7790989059818497`*^9}, {
  3.779098949086734*^9, 
  3.779098954831087*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"80741c1e-da9d-42d9-ad93-\
467295de6541"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Weaknesses", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.77909898223913*^9, 
  3.7790989880955772`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7c0dac79-9840-43e7-97e5-\
a8442b7b054f"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Strictly speaking, it is not learning anything. In other words, it does not \
provide a model which could be used to understand how the features are \
related to the class.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779099006264287*^9, 
  3.779099065724209*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ff2d8cc7-f4ae-4db3-8c98-\
c2b8c200f95b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Requires selection of an appropriate number of neighbours, ",
 StyleBox["k",
  FontSlant->"Italic"]
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779099006264287*^9, 3.7790990645292587`*^9}, {
  3.779099095313985*^9, 
  3.779099117953166*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6fef81d0-0b56-44f0-8b0c-\
cf9c20036a62"],

Cell["\<\
Although the training phase is fast, the classification phase can be slow. \
Indeed, one has to measure the distance between the new point and all the \
already-classified points.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779099006264287*^9, 3.7790990645292587`*^9}, {
  3.779099095313985*^9, 3.779099125906166*^9}, {3.779099996137336*^9, 
  3.7791000578139057`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"51cba7fa-1c29-4d67-b9e5-\
263d335698be"],

Cell["\<\
As every method based on distance between instances, it suffers from the \
curse of dimensionality.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.779099006264287*^9, 3.7790990645292587`*^9}, {
  3.779099095313985*^9, 3.779099125906166*^9}, {3.779099996137336*^9, 
  3.779100080395384*^9}, {3.779104601255332*^9, 
  3.77910460125561*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"de33bed1-4861-4a5f-bade-\
3d7054b7aa21"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
